CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 5, 1962, pg. A1 reads: "Headliners - Highlighting the recent NAACP Human Rights Dinner were these two notables, shown here with the branch president, Byrd R. Brown. Left is Pedro Sanjuan, assistant Chief of Protocol for the U.S. State Department, who was main speaker.  Right is Atty. Jack Greenberg, chief counsel for the national NAACP's Legal Defense and Educational Fund. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Pedro Sanjuan, Byrd R. Brown, and Atty. Jack Greenberg, seated in Penn Sheraton Hotel for NAACP Human Rights Dinner
